Job Description
Job Overview
We are looking for people with experience from risk management engineering within in the following domains:
• Well drilling • Subsea • Marine Systems • Process
Technical expertise within in one or more of our service areas are required:
• Risk management
- Audits
- HSE & Q management
- Emergency • Risk Analysis
- QRA
- HAZOP / HAZID / FMECA
- Barrier Analysis • Impact
- CFD
- Fire / Explosion analysis
- Exhaust study
- Flow analysis • Technical safety
- Process
- Fire protection • Working environment and human factors • Regularity and reliability studies • External environment
Job Responsibilities
Project management (internal R&D projects, JIP projects, consulting projects)
People management and mentoring
Resource management
Business development and thought leadership
Marketing
Job Requirements
To be successful in your application, you must: • Be proficient in your field • Have a postgraduate degree (e.g. MSc, PhD etc.) • Be outgoing, analytical and enjoy professional challenges and development • Thrive in project-based work • Build good relationships with customers • Posess commercial acumen • Be competitive • Act with honesty and integrity • Inspire, delight and bring out the best in others
